        <h5><center>Welcome to EquaWorld!<br></center></h5><h1>This is a website for: <br>-People being discriminated in any type of way at work
            <br>-Finding information on laws pertaining to discrimination
            <br>-Finding Lawyers who can represent you<br> </h1>
        <h3>Learn your rights to help combat the growing problem of discrimination!</h3>

        <h4>Employment discrimination happens when an employee or job applicant is treated unfavorably because of their race,
             skin color, national origin, gender, disability, religion, or age. Most prevalent in modern society are racism and sexism in the workplace, whose injustices are being targetted by organizations and movements such as the National Society for Black Engineers and Women in STEM.</h4><br>


        <p1><b> Examples of discrimination include</b><br>- denying certain employees compensation or benefits<br> -paying equally-qualified employees in the same position different salaries<br>- discriminating when assigning disability leave, maternity leave or retirement options<br> -denying use of company facilities.</p1>

